{# ── FAQ ── #}
<section class="section section--dark">
  <div class="container--narrow">
    <div class="section-header section-header--center">
      <span class="section-label">Questions</span>
      <h2>Merch FAQs</h2>
    </div>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-item__question">Do you handle printing and production?</summary>
      <div class="faq-item__answer"><p>We coordinate with print-on-demand partners (Printful, Printify) or direct printers depending on volume and timeline. We manage the vendor relationship, quality control, and delivery — you don't have to deal with it directly.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-item__question">Can you run my merch table at shows you're not already working?</summary>
      <div class="faq-item__answer"><p>Yes — merch operations is available as a standalone per-show service. Send us the show details and we'll scope out what merch table coverage looks like for that date.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-item__question">What if I already have a Shopify store?</summary>
      <div class="faq-item__answer"><p>We work within what you already have. If you have an existing store, we audit it, fix what isn't working, and integrate it with your in-person sales system so everything reports together.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-item__question">How do you charge for merch operations?</summary>
      <div class="faq-item__answer"><p>Setup is a flat project fee. Ongoing merch management and show-day operations are priced per show or as a monthly retainer depending on tour volume. We scope it clearly before anything starts.</p></div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

